Question: A tank of water has a depth of 17 feet on Monday. On Tuesday, the tank had 7 feet more water. On Wednesday, the depth of the water is two thirds of what it was on Tuesday. What is the tank‚Äôs water depth on Wednesday?
--------------------------------------------------
Generation:

To determine the depth of the water in the tank on Wednesday, we need to follow the steps given in the problem:

1. On Monday, the tank has a depth of 17 feet.
2. On Tuesday, the tank had 7 feet more water than on Monday.
3. On Wednesday, the depth of the water is two-thirds of what it was on Tuesday.

First, we calculate the depth of the water on Tuesday:
\[
text{Depth on Tuesday} = \text{Depth on Monday} + 7 \text{ feet} = 17 \text{ feet} + 7 \text{ feet} = 24 \text{ feet}
\]

Next, we calculate the depth of the water on Wednesday:
\[
\text{Depth on Wednesday} = \frac{2}{3} \times \text{Depth on Tuesday} = \frac{2}{3} \times 24 \text{ feet} = 16 \text{ feet}
\]

Therefore, the depth of the water on Wednesday is 16 feet.
</answer>
<answer>
\boxed{16}
</answer><|eot_id|><|endoftext|>
