Question: A tank of water has a depth of 17 feet on Monday. On Tuesday, the tank had 7 feet more water. On Wednesday, the depth of the water is two thirds of what it was on Tuesday. What is the tank‚Äôs water depth on Wednesday?
--------------------------------------------------
Generation:

1. We start with the depth of the water on Monday, which is 17 feet.
2. On Tuesday, the depth had increased by 7 feet compared to Monday. Therefore, the depth on Tuesday is:
   \[
   17 + 7 = 24 \text{ feet}
   \]
3. On Wednesday, the depth of the water is two-thirds of what it was on Tuesday. To find the depth on Wednesday, we calculate:
   \[
   \frac{2}{3} \times 24 = \frac{48}{3} \approx 16.33 \text{ feet}
   \]

